CLIMATE CHANGE & INFECTIOUS DISEASES (10): RECENT ARTICLES
===========================================================
Amsterdam: January 29, 1996

Dear ProMED users,

For your interest, here are some more recent titles on climate
change and infectious diseases.

I. Robert K. Dixon, Sandra Guill, Francis X. Mkanda, Ihor
Hlohowskyj (eds). Vulnerability and adaptation of African
ecosystems to global climate change (Special Edition).
Climate Research (ISSN 0936-577X), Volume 6, Number 2, 19
February 1996.

i. Martens WJM. Global atmospheric change and human
health: an integrated modelling approach.Clim-Res.
1996 Feb 19. 6(2). P 107-112.

ii. Patz JA, Balbus JM. Methods for assessing public
health vulnerability to global climate change.
Clim-Res. 1996 Feb 19. 6(2). P 113-125.

---------------------------------------------------------------
Tables-of-contents and tables-of-contents-with-abstracts of
Inter-Research journals are available free of charge on the
Internet via World Wide Web (http://www.int-res.com/int-res) or
via E-mail(contents@int-res.com).

Inter-Research, Nordbuente 23, D-21385 Oldendorf/Luhe, Germany
Tel: (+49)(0) 4132 7127
Fax: (+49)(0) 4132 8883
E-mail: ir@int-res.com
---------------------------------------------------------------


II. Patz J, Epstein PR, et al. Global climate change and
emerging infectious diseases. JAMA, vol. 375, no.3, 17
January 1996.
